How to create the bitmap images:
================================

* Create png from svg
=====================
- Open the file 'bndtools-swirl.svg' with Inkspace (I'm using version 0.48.1)
- Select in the menu: File->Export Bitmap
- Set the bitmap width to 2048 and the filename to swirl-2048.png
- Press the export button


* Create png image copy with glow
=================================
- Open the file 'swirl-2048.png' with GIMP (I'm using version 2.6.11)
- Select in the menu: Filters->Light and Shadow->Gradient Flare...
- Select the 'Default' entry on the 'Selector' tab, as shown in the
  'Gradient Flare - Selector.png' screenshot
- Use the settings as shown in the 'Gradient Flare - Settings.png' screenshot
- Select in the menu: File->Save As...
- Set the filename to 'swirl-glow-2048.png' and press the 'Save' button, use the
  save settings as shown in the 'Save as PNG.png' screenshot

You now have the large versions (regular and glow) of the bitmaps.


* Scale images
==============
- Open the file 'swirl-2048.png' with GIMP
- Select in the menu: Image->Scale Image...
- Set the width to 512 and press the 'Scale' button
- Select in the menu: File->Save As...
- Set the filename to 'swirl-512.png' and press the 'Save' button, use the
  save settings as shown in the 'Save as PNG.png' screenshot
- Select in the menu: Edit->Undo Scale Image
- Repeat (go to second step of the above procedure) for all other sizes

- Repeat the above procedure for the 'swirl-glow-2048.png' file


* Create 512x512 images
=======================
- Open the file 'swirl-512.png' with GIMP
- Select in the menu: Image->Canvas Size...
- Click the chain icon next to the 'Width' and 'Height' fields to unlock
  the fields, set the 'Height' to 512, click the 'Center' button, and finally
  click the 'Resize' button
- Select in the menu: File->Save As...
- Set the filename to 'swirl-512x512.png' and press the 'Save' button, use the
  save settings as shown in the 'Save as PNG.png' screenshot

- Repeat the above procedure for the 'swirl-glow-512.png' file


* Create Eclipse welcome page icons
===================================
- Open the file 'swirl-48.png' with GIMP
- Select in the menu: File->Save As...
- Set the filename to 'bndtools.gif' and press the 'Save' button, press the
  'Export' botton, and finally press the 'Save' button

- Repeat the above procedure for the 'swirl-glow-48.png' file, but name it
  'bndtools-glow.gif'.

- Move both these gif images into the bndtools.core/resources/intro/images
  directory

